results.name: Zero through ten in alphabetical order of English reverse spelling.
example: a(1) = 3 because EERHT comes alphabetically first.
a(2) = 9 because ENIN comes alphabetically second.
a(3) = 1 because ENO comes alphabetically third.
a(4) = 5 because EVIF comes alphabetically fourth.
results.author: _Jonathan Vos Post_, Jul 30 2006
